WEBVTT

00:02.252 --> 00:03.420
Hello, Kenneth.
Where were you guys?

00:03.420 --> 00:05.464
You missed my jazz brunch.
I mean, good,

00:05.464 --> 00:07.090
but what are you
talking about?

00:07.090 --> 00:10.302
I cook a delicious meal
and curate jazz for my guests.

00:10.302 --> 00:12.262
[ Chuckles ]
It is a happening.

00:12.262 --> 00:13.805
The cats dig it the most.

00:13.805 --> 00:16.475
It also takes me a few days
after to drop the lingo, man.

00:16.475 --> 00:17.893
I mailed you an invitation.

00:17.893 --> 00:19.603
Yeah.
Sorry, Kenneth.

00:19.603 --> 00:20.896
Lots of
important things

00:20.896 --> 00:22.523
have been slipping through
the cracks recently.

00:22.523 --> 00:24.358
And also
a jazz brunch.

00:24.358 --> 00:25.734
Do we have a problem?

00:25.734 --> 00:29.488
Okay, I think it might be time
for a purge.

00:30.197 --> 00:31.156
We doing it?

00:32.449 --> 00:34.201
Right. All Mails Day.

00:34.201 --> 00:36.203
Snail mail, e‐mails,
voicemail ‐‐

00:36.203 --> 00:37.287
We'll get it all done
in one swoop,

00:37.287 --> 00:38.580
and then decide
who to call back.

00:38.580 --> 00:40.499
Maya and I
will take cellphones.

00:40.499 --> 00:44.336
On snail mail, it's Dylan.
On e‐mail, it's Ray.

00:44.336 --> 00:48.298
And with ancient answering
machine, here's Jimmy Jr.

00:48.298 --> 00:50.968
Oh, DiMeos. Is there nothing
you can't make slightly fun?

00:50.968 --> 00:53.679
And go.
Hey, we're pre‐approved
for a credit card.

00:53.679 --> 00:54.680
Fools.

00:54.680 --> 00:55.806
Red‐light ticket, Mom.

00:55.806 --> 00:57.474
Ooh, I look fantastic.
Save that.

00:57.474 --> 01:00.686
Ray:
Delete, delete, delete, delete.

01:00.686 --> 01:02.187
Oh, Aunt Molly died.

01:02.187 --> 01:03.730
Uncle Frank had a baby.
It's a push.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.482
Looks like we got
a school letter.

01:05.482 --> 01:06.692
Oh, school e‐mail.

01:06.692 --> 01:07.526
It's from...
JJ's history teacher...

01:07.526 --> 01:09.194
...Mr. Powers.
... Mr. Powers.

01:09.194 --> 01:11.488
[ On all devices ] Mr. Powers:
<i>Hi, there. This is Mr. Powers,</i>

01:11.488 --> 01:12.823
<i>JJ's history teacher.</i>

01:12.823 --> 01:14.658
<i>Could you please</i>
<i>give me a call?</i>

01:14.658 --> 01:17.369
<i>I'd like to have</i>
<i>a talk about JJ, okay? Bye‐bye!</i>

01:17.369 --> 01:18.829
[ Answering machine beeps ]

01:18.829 --> 01:21.081
We will call him back first,
oh, Lord.

01:27.337 --> 01:29.715
Oh, Mrs. DiMeo,
you look... hot.

01:29.715 --> 01:30.757
What's the occasion?

01:30.757 --> 01:32.134
"Call My Wife Hot" Day?

01:32.134 --> 01:33.510
Oh, thank you, Kenneth.

01:33.510 --> 01:35.012
I connected with
that teacher.

01:35.012 --> 01:36.513
I am dressed
for my first conference

01:36.513 --> 01:38.098
about JJ
in a mainstream school.

01:38.098 --> 01:40.726
Will it be of the "Ray needs to
skip a grade" variety

01:40.726 --> 01:42.936
or the "Dylan lured another
raccoon into class" variety?

01:42.936 --> 01:44.229
Only time will tell.

01:44.229 --> 01:46.064
Those little guys <i>beg</i> me
to come in.

01:46.064 --> 01:48.275
Ah, yeah!
Today's the day!

01:48.275 --> 01:49.818
I say "career,"
you say "fair."

01:49.818 --> 01:51.111
Career.
Fair.

01:51.111 --> 01:53.071
Career.
I'm sorry. You only get one.

01:53.071 --> 01:54.531
Why are you so excited
about the career fair?

01:54.531 --> 01:56.658
Because today's the day
I figure out

01:56.658 --> 01:59.745
which career is gonna make
Ray DiMeo Ray DiMillionaire.

01:59.745 --> 02:01.830
Well, if you're cool with it
taking several centuries,

02:01.830 --> 02:03.290
stop by my booth.

02:03.290 --> 02:04.541
Why are you even
doing the fair, Dad?

02:04.541 --> 02:05.876
It's not like working
at the airport

02:05.876 --> 02:07.502
is flashy or high‐paying.

02:07.502 --> 02:09.963
There are things
that matter besides money,

02:09.963 --> 02:11.256
like passion for the work.

02:11.256 --> 02:12.382
You don't have that, either.

02:12.382 --> 02:13.967
No, but
the commute's good.

02:14.635 --> 02:15.969
Commute's okay.

02:15.969 --> 02:18.305
♪♪

02:18.305 --> 02:20.140
But the best part
of my job

02:20.140 --> 02:21.808
is the moment when you introduce
the child

02:21.808 --> 02:23.101
to its new service animal,

02:23.101 --> 02:25.020
and, in an instant,
the child knows it's safe.

02:25.020 --> 02:27.189
Cool.
How much do you make?

02:27.189 --> 02:29.358
♪ The best things in life
are free ♪
Do you like the idea

02:29.358 --> 02:31.568
of helping cool brands
connect to their audience?

02:31.568 --> 02:34.529
Let me answer your question
with a question.

02:34.529 --> 02:35.947
How much do you make?

02:35.947 --> 02:37.783
So, how much
do you make?

02:37.783 --> 02:40.077
I told you ‐‐ I'm a volunteer
for a charity.

02:40.077 --> 02:41.620
I make zero dollars.

02:41.620 --> 02:43.705
You realize asking strangers
how much they make

02:43.705 --> 02:44.998
is incredibly rude.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.792
Okay, how much
do you make?

02:46.792 --> 02:48.543
As you were.

02:48.543 --> 02:51.004
I'm sorry it took us so long
to get in touch.

02:51.004 --> 02:52.673
Perhaps next time
there's a message,

02:52.673 --> 02:54.716
we can make Kenneth
our little carrier pigeon.

02:54.716 --> 02:57.803
Huh. Perhaps we should see
what happens if you try that.

02:57.803 --> 02:59.471
Right,
to the matter at hand.

02:59.471 --> 03:02.057
I have received
some complaints

03:02.057 --> 03:04.309
about JJ
from the other students.

03:04.309 --> 03:05.602
They're jealous.

03:05.602 --> 03:07.896
They are... of his constant,

03:07.896 --> 03:11.441
unpunished,
insanely obvious cheating.

03:11.441 --> 03:12.109
What?!
What?!

03:12.109 --> 03:13.402
W‐H‐‐ "What?!"

03:13.402 --> 03:15.570
That's ridiculous.
JJ cheating?

03:15.570 --> 03:17.364
How?
I'm on him all the time.

03:17.364 --> 03:18.907
Do I strike you
as the kind of person

03:18.907 --> 03:20.701
who's looking for conflict
with any of you?

03:20.701 --> 03:22.911
I mean, between liberal guilt
and good old‐fashioned terror,

03:22.911 --> 03:24.371
I look at the three of you

03:24.371 --> 03:25.914
and just pray
that if I roll on my back,

03:25.914 --> 03:27.749
someone will rub my tummy.

03:27.749 --> 03:29.376
Is he a real teacher here?
Hmm.

03:29.376 --> 03:30.836
But I know what I saw.

03:30.836 --> 03:34.089
JJ got a 92% on that test
and he did not earn it.

03:34.089 --> 03:35.340
JJ is innocent.

03:35.340 --> 03:36.591
If you think
he didn't deserve the grade,

03:36.591 --> 03:37.759
make him take the test again
right now.

03:37.759 --> 03:38.635
Fine.

03:40.345 --> 03:42.222
You really do look nice.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.390
What is it ‐‐
your ‐‐ your hair, or...

03:43.390 --> 03:44.391
What is this?

03:44.391 --> 03:45.851
How do you think
I normally look?

03:45.851 --> 03:47.519
[ Chuckles ] You know.

03:47.519 --> 03:49.396
♪♪

03:49.396 --> 03:50.439
What career are you?

03:50.439 --> 03:52.107
It's actually
more of a job ‐‐

03:52.107 --> 03:54.192
airport baggage handling
supervisor.

03:55.610 --> 03:57.946
Okay, have fun checking out
other careers.

03:57.946 --> 04:00.073
I'm sure they all let you keep
unclaimed luggage

04:00.073 --> 04:02.325
after the 90‐day
waiting period.

04:02.325 --> 04:04.286
Oh, oh, do I have
your attention now?

04:04.286 --> 04:06.288
That's right.
Who wants a suitcase?

04:06.288 --> 04:09.624
The RIMOWA, hard case,
with international stickers.

04:09.624 --> 04:11.334
I have trained you well.

04:13.795 --> 04:15.714
These look stupid.

04:15.714 --> 04:17.257
Ugh, they smell awful.

04:17.257 --> 04:19.468
[ Sniffs ]

04:19.468 --> 04:20.719
Wait. Just me.

04:20.719 --> 04:24.473
Well, I guess
I dress like this now.

04:24.473 --> 04:27.434
♪♪

04:29.644 --> 04:32.230
Hello, Dolly.

04:32.230 --> 04:35.275
That is my
favorite piece.

04:35.275 --> 04:36.777
You have
a very good eye.

04:36.777 --> 04:38.028
Thank you.

04:38.028 --> 04:39.988
So, uh,
you sell jewelry?

04:39.988 --> 04:42.032
Well [chuckles]
what we really sell here

04:42.032 --> 04:43.825
at Kingsley & Kate
is a lifestyle.

04:43.825 --> 04:45.786
We are
a multi‐level marketing company

04:45.786 --> 04:48.038
that lets anyone ‐‐
even young people like you ‐‐

04:48.038 --> 04:49.372
become sales ambassadors.

04:49.372 --> 04:51.708
Here's how it works.

04:51.708 --> 04:53.835
Cool diagram.
It looks like a pyramid.

04:53.835 --> 04:54.836
I don't see it.

04:55.462 --> 04:56.880
Yasmin.

04:56.880 --> 04:58.507
Ray.

04:58.507 --> 05:02.093
So, Yasmin, let me ask you
one final question.

05:02.093 --> 05:03.637
How much do you make?

05:03.637 --> 05:06.139
Jewelry is considered
the strongest industry ever,

05:06.139 --> 05:08.308
and with our
dynamic sales approach,

05:08.308 --> 05:10.227
a Kingsley & Kate
ambassador

05:10.227 --> 05:12.687
can literally make
an infinite salary.

05:12.687 --> 05:14.689
Whoa.

05:14.689 --> 05:16.566
I got a bunch of bags
of dried pineapple

05:16.566 --> 05:17.734
and picture of some kid.

05:17.734 --> 05:18.693
Sweet haul, Nadia.

05:18.693 --> 05:20.237
I want to be
a baggage handler.

05:20.237 --> 05:22.072
Ray, are you in this
throng of adoring teens?

05:22.072 --> 05:23.406
You seeing this triumph?

05:23.406 --> 05:26.201
♪♪

05:26.201 --> 05:29.037
How can I be upset
at someone so gorgeous?

05:30.872 --> 05:32.916
Your top's ratchet.
Where's it from?

05:32.916 --> 05:34.626
Career fair suitcase.

05:34.626 --> 05:37.462
We don't know what that is,
but we like you.

05:37.462 --> 05:39.297
Of course you do.
I'm awesome.

05:41.883 --> 05:43.301
Hey.

05:43.301 --> 05:45.720
Your fries are ratchet.

05:45.720 --> 05:47.389
Okay,
you have 30 minutes.

05:47.389 --> 05:48.974
Oh, hang on.

05:48.974 --> 05:50.851
To eliminate all possibility
of cheating ‐‐

05:50.851 --> 05:52.477
Attention, please!

05:52.477 --> 05:55.730
All other students
leave the room now.

05:56.773 --> 05:58.942
Go ahead.
Okay.

05:58.942 --> 06:02.863
"What decorated veteran
was the first general‐in‐chief

06:02.863 --> 06:04.197
of the Union army?"

06:05.615 --> 06:07.534
"C"?
Are you sure?

06:09.327 --> 06:10.287
"B"?

06:12.873 --> 06:14.457
"A"?

06:14.457 --> 06:15.959
All right,
well, your wish is my command.

06:15.959 --> 06:17.377
Okay, next question.
Mm‐hmm.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.170
"D"? Okay.

06:19.170 --> 06:22.591
Writing "D" unless,
maybe...

06:22.591 --> 06:24.050
Oi!
Jazz brunch.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.135
[ Whispering ]
Maya, shh.

06:25.135 --> 06:26.344
JJ's taking a test.

06:26.344 --> 06:27.554
No,
you're taking the test!

06:27.554 --> 06:29.973
You are giving him
all the bloody answers.

06:29.973 --> 06:31.766
Me?!
Yeah, you.

06:31.766 --> 06:33.768
[ Imitating Kenneth ]
"A"? You sure it's not "B"?
'Cause it's "B".

06:33.768 --> 06:35.228
[ Normal voice ]
And you are cheating.

06:35.228 --> 06:37.898
You're cheating off me?
That's awful.

06:37.898 --> 06:39.357
It's also
a bit flattering.

06:39.357 --> 06:40.984
No one's ever cheated off me
before.

06:40.984 --> 06:42.944
I wasn't much of a student
in high school, so ‐‐

06:42.944 --> 06:44.487
I don't know her very well,

06:44.487 --> 06:46.281
but I don't think
she cares about this.

06:46.281 --> 06:48.241
We owe you
a tremendous apology.

06:48.241 --> 06:50.285
I‐I‐I don't how
you're not gloating.

06:50.285 --> 06:51.578
You must be
a very good person.

06:51.578 --> 06:53.538
I am a Buddhist.
We can talk later.

06:54.456 --> 06:55.707
Maya: <i>You</i> wanted
to be challenged,

06:55.707 --> 06:57.375
<i>you</i> wanted to be
put in a mainstream school,

06:57.375 --> 06:58.960
and now you're wasting it.

06:58.960 --> 07:00.629
No, this ends now.
Let's go.

07:00.629 --> 07:03.506
♪♪

07:03.506 --> 07:05.008
Kenneth: So, basically,
I took that test.

07:05.008 --> 07:06.092
You said it was a 92%?
Now.

07:09.679 --> 07:10.764
My son cheating.

07:10.764 --> 07:12.432
Did you do all his bloody
homework for him, as well?

07:12.432 --> 07:14.059
No! I have nothing to do
with the homework.

07:14.059 --> 07:15.852
The stuff I learned
is just from listening in class.

07:15.852 --> 07:18.813
Hmm. Imagine if I actually
<i>did</i> do the homework.

07:18.813 --> 07:21.858
You're a smart kid, JJ.
It's time to apply yourself.

07:21.858 --> 07:23.485
Okay, let's take a look
at your homework log.

07:23.485 --> 07:24.361
Put in your password.

07:25.612 --> 07:26.988
Do you not know
the password?

07:26.988 --> 07:28.198
When was the last time
you logged in?

07:29.240 --> 07:31.660
You don't do any
of your homework at all?

07:31.660 --> 07:33.161
Well, you're back here
on the computer all the time.

07:33.161 --> 07:34.204
Doing what?

07:34.204 --> 07:36.706
Right, I am checking
your search history.

07:36.706 --> 07:38.917
No, no, no, no, no. Don't check
a man's search history.

07:38.917 --> 07:41.336
Oh, JJ, I'm sorry.
I led us down this road.

07:41.336 --> 07:43.630
"Emma Watson,"
"Emma Watson hot,"

07:43.630 --> 07:47.884
"Emma Watson
wheelchair‐user boyfriend?"

07:49.094 --> 07:52.055
It's a beautiful thing ‐‐
hope.

07:52.055 --> 07:54.224
So, clearly,
you're not doing any work

07:54.224 --> 07:55.892
and your teachers
are letting you slide.

07:55.892 --> 07:57.143
How does that
make you feel?

07:57.894 --> 08:00.271
"I didn't ask them.

08:00.271 --> 08:02.816
They cut me s‐slack.

08:02.816 --> 08:04.734
Why say no?"

08:04.734 --> 08:07.070
Because it's wrong. Because
you are better than that.

08:07.070 --> 08:09.531
God, I've never been
so horrified.

08:09.531 --> 08:12.367
Horrified at the price
of today's designer jewelry?

08:12.367 --> 08:13.451
I am, too.

08:13.451 --> 08:15.537
Yeah, whatever this is,
I'm gonna pass.

08:16.955 --> 08:19.249
Look, your ensemble
is fantastic.

08:19.249 --> 08:21.084
I just ‐‐ I feel like
there's one piece missing

08:21.084 --> 08:22.794
to make it all pop.
Really?

08:22.794 --> 08:24.254
Have you heard of
Kingsley & Kate?

08:24.254 --> 08:26.089
Oh, that awful
jewelry company?

08:26.089 --> 08:27.882
[ Laughing ]
That stuff is hideous.

08:27.882 --> 08:30.176
I was asking her!
Ugh!

08:30.176 --> 08:32.470
So, Mom, say,
I was thinking about

08:32.470 --> 08:34.848
our conversation about
Kingsley & Kate.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.891
Did you know
that they hire top designers

08:36.891 --> 08:39.102
to handcraft styles
for any occasion?
[ Sighs ]

08:39.102 --> 08:40.311
No.

08:40.311 --> 08:42.188
Ray!

08:42.188 --> 08:43.523
Say, would you
like to continue

08:43.523 --> 08:45.066
this conversation
in the backyard?

08:47.277 --> 08:48.528
What have you done?

08:48.528 --> 08:50.363
I became
a brand ambassador.

08:50.363 --> 08:53.158
You became a sucker
in a pyramid scheme.

08:53.158 --> 08:55.035
God, those are really ugly,
aren't they?

08:55.035 --> 08:57.078
How much have you sold?
None.

08:57.078 --> 08:59.789
Nobody appreciates fine jewelry
in this Podunk town.

08:59.789 --> 09:01.166
I'm screwed.

09:01.166 --> 09:03.710
[ Sighs ] So I guess we're gonna
have to buy this crap

09:03.710 --> 09:05.045
and bail you out.

09:05.045 --> 09:06.212
How much you
on the hook for?

09:06.212 --> 09:07.338
500 bucks.

09:07.338 --> 09:09.257
We don't have
that kind of money lying around.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.259
Oh, Jimmy, you're gonna have
to become a gigolo.

09:11.259 --> 09:12.469
I'm worried that'd be
almost too lucrative.

09:12.469 --> 09:14.804
♪♪

09:14.804 --> 09:17.348
Hey, Shelby,
glad you're feeling better.

09:17.348 --> 09:18.933
So, who's trying
to dress like us?

09:20.685 --> 09:22.604
Look, I‐I don't know
who you are.

09:22.604 --> 09:24.481
I don't even know
who they are.

09:24.481 --> 09:27.442
They think that I'm gonna ask.
I ain't.

09:27.442 --> 09:30.111
But I can assure you,
<i>this</i>

09:30.111 --> 09:31.404
isn't a look
I'm trying to copy.

09:35.700 --> 09:37.494
Wait up, you guys!

09:37.494 --> 09:39.621
Good afternoon.
Your attention, please.

09:39.621 --> 09:41.664
We have bombarded
your safe place

09:41.664 --> 09:43.541
for reasons
I cannot truly justify

09:43.541 --> 09:46.002
other than the fact I
love the element of surprise.

09:46.002 --> 09:47.545
Now, you know
my son JJ.

09:47.545 --> 09:49.255
You've all been very generous
with his grades.

09:49.255 --> 09:50.381
Too generous.

09:50.381 --> 09:52.092
You're giving him marks
he has not earned.

09:52.092 --> 09:53.718
That's ridiculous!
No.

09:53.718 --> 09:55.470
Oh, come on.
We're all guilty.

09:55.470 --> 09:57.514
Yes, it's easier
to let him slide,

09:57.514 --> 09:59.349
but to do so
would be to rob JJ

09:59.349 --> 10:01.684
of the chance to realize
his true potential.

10:01.684 --> 10:03.436
You suck.
Oh, I suck?

10:03.436 --> 10:05.313
Whoever said that sucks.

10:05.313 --> 10:07.607
JJ does not want
preferential treatment.

10:07.607 --> 10:08.441
Do you, JJ?

10:09.943 --> 10:11.611
"Starting next year."

10:11.611 --> 10:13.404
No, now.
Ignore that.

10:13.404 --> 10:15.365
So just to be clear,
we shouldn't give him

10:15.365 --> 10:17.367
the answers to the questions
before the test?

10:17.367 --> 10:18.743
No, of course not.

10:18.743 --> 10:20.245
It's okay he ain't
take the test?

10:20.245 --> 10:21.496
Don't you teach
English here?

10:21.496 --> 10:22.664
Not in no lounge.

10:22.664 --> 10:24.165
Well, if he ain't
take the test,

10:24.165 --> 10:25.750
he fails the test,
all right?

10:25.750 --> 10:27.293
How is this okay?

10:27.293 --> 10:30.296
In fairness, he's a great kid,
and he's clearly very bright,

10:30.296 --> 10:33.341
but, I mean,
he deals with a lot.

10:33.341 --> 10:34.634
I certainly don't want to
give him a "D".

10:36.219 --> 10:38.763
"You think I'd get a 'D'?"

10:38.763 --> 10:40.056
Why would he get a "D"?

10:40.056 --> 10:43.768
"If I tried,
I wouldn't get a 'D'."

10:43.768 --> 10:45.478
Finally, bit of pride.

10:45.478 --> 10:49.023
"I'll ace the next test.
You'll see."

10:49.023 --> 10:50.275
[ Chuckles ]
That's right, JJ.

10:50.275 --> 10:51.609
You're gonna do great,
man.

10:51.609 --> 10:52.986
You're going to do well.

10:52.986 --> 10:54.237
♪♪

10:54.237 --> 10:56.197
Ray:
Who are all these people?

10:56.197 --> 10:57.866
Jimmy:
This is your trunk show.

10:57.866 --> 10:59.534
I can't sell this crap
to my friends.

10:59.534 --> 11:01.286
They'd never want to
see me again.

11:01.286 --> 11:02.745
That's okay
with this crowd.

11:02.745 --> 11:05.373
This is my "I don't need to see
<i>you</i> again" list.

11:05.373 --> 11:06.875
That's excellent.

11:06.875 --> 11:08.042
There's the guy
from jury duty

11:08.042 --> 11:09.377
who I was supposed to have
coffee with.

11:09.377 --> 11:11.921
Our former mailman.

11:11.921 --> 11:13.506
Drunk guy
from the airplane

11:13.506 --> 11:15.133
who I became
Facebook friends with.

11:15.133 --> 11:16.843
'Sup, Frank?

11:16.843 --> 11:18.428
I just called him
by the wrong name.

11:18.428 --> 11:20.805
I should be embarrassed.
I feel nothing.

11:20.805 --> 11:21.764
Let's do this.

11:23.057 --> 11:24.893
Yes!
He's killing it.

11:24.893 --> 11:26.519
Hey, what are you doing? Aren't
you supposed to be studying?

11:26.519 --> 11:27.937
Yeah, watch.

11:27.937 --> 11:31.441
Okay, JJ, a crazed fan
has kidnapped Emma Watson.

11:31.441 --> 11:32.942
He will only free her

11:32.942 --> 11:34.861
if you can name
the first five states ‐‐

11:34.861 --> 11:36.613
in order ‐‐
to secede from the Union.

11:36.613 --> 11:37.488
Go!

11:37.488 --> 11:38.489
Blam!

11:38.489 --> 11:39.490
Blips!

11:39.490 --> 11:40.325
Plow!

11:41.159 --> 11:42.493
Unh!

11:42.493 --> 11:43.745
Yeah!

11:43.745 --> 11:44.954
Dude's crushing it.

11:44.954 --> 11:46.372
Well done, sweetheart.

11:46.372 --> 11:47.582
By the way,
did you notice

11:47.582 --> 11:49.125
that I didn't even
have to check the book

11:49.125 --> 11:50.126
to see if he was right?

11:51.252 --> 11:52.837
Just jealous.

11:52.837 --> 11:54.631
Giovanni,
my former landlord.

11:54.631 --> 11:57.050
Love the Christmas cards ‐‐
keep them coming.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.468
Hey, guy!

11:58.468 --> 12:00.094
Al, it has been too long
since we were stuck

12:00.094 --> 12:01.554
in an elevator during
that earthquake.

12:01.554 --> 12:03.723
Good to see you.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.016
Doug?
Hey, Jimmy.

12:05.016 --> 12:06.100
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
You're Cool Doug.

12:06.100 --> 12:07.477
I meant to invite
Bummer Doug.

12:07.477 --> 12:08.645
No, no, no, no.

12:08.645 --> 12:10.188
Yeah, you don't belong here.
I'll call you.

12:10.188 --> 12:12.690
I'll call you.
[ Bell rings ]

12:12.690 --> 12:15.902
Hello, everyone.
Thank you all for coming.

12:15.902 --> 12:18.529
I'd like to offer you
a special opportunity

12:18.529 --> 12:20.782
to buy some fine jewelry

12:20.782 --> 12:23.451
inspired by
the runways of Paris.

12:23.451 --> 12:25.912
I'm not here to buy jewelry.
I'm here to party.

12:25.912 --> 12:26.871
Jimmy,
you got any snacks?

12:26.871 --> 12:28.831
Here's a loaf of bread.

12:28.831 --> 12:32.418
Like I was saying, inspired
by the runways of Paris.

12:36.089 --> 12:39.217
Okay.
Let's get real here for a sec.

12:39.217 --> 12:43.221
You're all of a sudden too good
for my son's jewelry? Nuh‐uh.

12:43.221 --> 12:45.556
You came to a party
hosted by a guy

12:45.556 --> 12:48.393
you haven't seen in years
on three hours' notice.

12:48.393 --> 12:49.936
You're bored.

12:49.936 --> 12:52.397
Don't buy this jewelry
because you like it,

12:52.397 --> 12:55.024
buy it because
it's something to do.

12:55.024 --> 12:57.735
I see you thinking about it,
Dylan's old karate teacher.

12:57.735 --> 12:59.946
Yeah!

13:01.072 --> 13:03.950
Okay, now it's a party.

13:03.950 --> 13:05.451
Got any drinks?

13:05.451 --> 13:07.537
I have one beer.
Take a sip, pass it around.

13:07.537 --> 13:09.539
We sold everything, Dad.

13:09.539 --> 13:11.124
That's, like,
the most amazing thing

13:11.124 --> 13:12.667
you've ever done
in your life.

13:12.667 --> 13:15.461
Aww, you are the king of
undercutting a compliment.

13:15.461 --> 13:16.587
You gonna pay back
Yasmin?

13:16.587 --> 13:18.756
Even better.
I ordered more jewelry.

13:18.756 --> 13:20.717
What?
Twice as much.

13:20.717 --> 13:24.971
Twice as much jewelry means
twice as much of this.

13:24.971 --> 13:27.640
Who are you?

13:27.640 --> 13:29.767
[ Sniffs ]
Smells like your body wash.

13:29.767 --> 13:30.685
Have you been rolling around
in this?

13:30.685 --> 13:31.894
Mnh‐mnh.

13:31.894 --> 13:33.354
It's over.
We're done.

13:33.354 --> 13:35.440
Why? Why walk away from
the one thing you're good at?

13:35.440 --> 13:37.692
I'm sorry?
You said it.

13:37.692 --> 13:39.527
You don't like your job
and you don't make good money.

13:39.527 --> 13:41.988
Yeah, stop caring
so much about money.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.531
You could stand
to care about it more, Dad.

13:43.531 --> 13:46.117
There's nothing wrong
with a little drive.

13:46.117 --> 13:47.994
Enough.
You're grounded for two weeks.

13:47.994 --> 13:50.121
But I don't ‐‐
I don't go anywhere.

13:50.121 --> 13:51.873
Fine.
Then two weeks of partying.

13:51.873 --> 13:53.124
Just get out.

13:53.124 --> 13:55.376
Have a great day,
darling.

13:55.376 --> 13:56.919
Ooh, your sweater's
on backwards.

13:56.919 --> 13:58.671
Who cares?
It'll look bad either way.

13:58.671 --> 14:03.092
♪♪

14:03.092 --> 14:05.178
Come on, Ray.
Don't leave a mother hanging.

14:07.638 --> 14:08.765
Mwah.

14:08.765 --> 14:09.807
And you.

14:11.350 --> 14:13.978
Today is the day
that you prove to the world

14:13.978 --> 14:16.647
you can do anything
you set your mind to.

14:16.647 --> 14:17.774
It's just the beginning.

14:17.774 --> 14:19.192
You're gonna
get great grades,

14:19.192 --> 14:20.443
you're gonna go to
a great college,

14:20.443 --> 14:21.736
you're gonna have
a great job,

14:21.736 --> 14:23.780
and you're gonna have
a great life...

14:23.780 --> 14:25.239
that you earned yourself.

14:27.033 --> 14:30.119
Okay, and it all begins
with you crushing this exam.

14:30.119 --> 14:32.538
Okay?

14:32.538 --> 14:35.708
♪♪

14:39.295 --> 14:40.880
[ Engine starts ]

14:52.308 --> 14:55.353
♪♪

14:55.353 --> 14:57.814
Dude!
Let's go ‐‐ your test.

14:57.814 --> 15:00.274
And once that's done with,

15:00.274 --> 15:01.567
we're gonna work on
your hiding skills.

15:03.694 --> 15:06.405
"Do you think
I'll do well?"

15:06.405 --> 15:08.449
Yeah, man,
you're ‐‐ you're gonna kill it.

15:10.660 --> 15:14.247
"I know your tells,
remember?"

15:14.247 --> 15:15.832
Right.

15:15.832 --> 15:18.042
"What if I'm dumb?"

15:18.042 --> 15:20.962
Whoa, whoa,
JJ, fine, okay.

15:20.962 --> 15:23.714
Maybe I don't know
if you're gonna <i>kill</i> this test,

15:23.714 --> 15:25.675
but I'm with you
all the time.

15:25.675 --> 15:26.717
I'm in your head.

15:26.717 --> 15:27.969
Dude, you're not dumb.

15:28.886 --> 15:30.555
Let's go do this.

15:30.555 --> 15:33.349
You know what? There is one
thing you are dumb about ‐‐

15:33.349 --> 15:35.101
clearing
your search history.

15:35.101 --> 15:36.769
Come on, man!

15:36.769 --> 15:37.645
Erase that cache.

15:37.645 --> 15:39.063
Let's go.

15:40.148 --> 15:42.567
Hey, Dylan!
Check it out!

15:42.567 --> 15:44.152
Whoo!

15:44.152 --> 15:45.194
For Pete's sake.

15:46.904 --> 15:48.614
Listen up, everyone!

15:48.614 --> 15:52.451
Yes, I wore my sweater
backwards, but it was a mistake,

15:52.451 --> 15:55.830
and I pull it off,
but that doesn't make it cool.

15:55.830 --> 15:57.498
So, then, what is cool,
Dylan?

15:57.498 --> 15:59.709
I don't know.
I don't think about that.

15:59.709 --> 16:01.377
That's what makes me cool.

16:02.753 --> 16:04.755
That's the lesson ‐‐
don't worry about

16:04.755 --> 16:07.049
what other people think
and you'll be cool.

16:07.049 --> 16:08.467
Can I get a teacher
to back me up?

16:10.678 --> 16:12.054
Even you, Mr. Powers?

16:14.140 --> 16:15.516
Okay, you.

16:15.516 --> 16:17.643
Tell me something you've <i>always</i>
wanted to wear.

16:17.643 --> 16:20.396
I want to wear sandals all year,
even in the winter.

16:20.396 --> 16:21.689
Okay.

16:21.689 --> 16:23.149
You see,
that's really weird,

16:23.149 --> 16:24.442
but who cares what I think,
right?

16:24.442 --> 16:25.902
That's the whole point.

16:25.902 --> 16:27.111
What ‐‐ What about you?

16:27.111 --> 16:28.863
I always wanted to
wear a beret.
Okay.

16:28.863 --> 16:33.576
Another really bad example,
but you do you.

16:33.576 --> 16:36.495
Who else?
Baseball pants
for normal pants.

16:36.495 --> 16:38.122
Fanny packs.
Girl: A duster.

16:38.122 --> 16:40.166
A yarmulke. Why should only
Jewish kids get to wear them?

16:40.166 --> 16:42.585
Wigs!
Real fur!

16:42.585 --> 16:45.087
Okay.

16:45.087 --> 16:47.757
I thought being ‐‐
being yourself was the answer,

16:47.757 --> 16:49.592
but apparently that's only true
if you're me.

16:49.592 --> 16:52.345
New plan ‐‐ From now on,
I decide what you wear.

16:52.345 --> 16:55.056
We all wear blue tomorrow.
Got it?

16:55.056 --> 16:56.557
Sorry. Would, like,
an aqua shade...

16:57.767 --> 16:58.768
Blue. We'll just...

16:58.768 --> 17:01.145
Okay, class, you may begin.

17:01.145 --> 17:02.146
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:07.735 --> 17:09.111
[ Sighs ]

17:13.199 --> 17:16.535
Mr. Powers, um,
there's an extra test.

17:16.535 --> 17:21.499
Seems a little, you know,
silly just to waste it here.

17:22.667 --> 17:23.668
Don't mind me.

17:25.127 --> 17:26.587
Ray: Why are we here?

17:26.587 --> 17:28.714
Did you change your mind about
selling more jewelry?

17:28.714 --> 17:30.091
I'm got some
creative ideas

17:30.091 --> 17:31.551
on how we could
up‐sell to single moms.

17:32.718 --> 17:35.721
You see that building?
Those windows? That's me.

17:36.806 --> 17:38.641
This other guy
wanted them to be

17:38.641 --> 17:40.393
about 2 inches wider ‐‐
wrong.

17:40.393 --> 17:42.061
Those windows
are perfect.

17:42.061 --> 17:44.939
I'm sorry.
Y‐You designed a building?

17:44.939 --> 17:46.649
I was studying architecture,

17:46.649 --> 17:48.943
and I was interning
at this big firm,

17:48.943 --> 17:51.654
then, you know,
your mom and I had a baby,

17:51.654 --> 17:54.282
and I needed insurance <i>now,</i>
something solid <i>now,</i>

17:54.282 --> 17:56.576
not something great later.

17:56.576 --> 17:59.829
So, you know,
family beat windows,

17:59.829 --> 18:02.164
but at least the ones
I did...

18:02.164 --> 18:03.708
are perfect.

18:03.708 --> 18:05.751
I think
they'd be better wider.

18:05.751 --> 18:07.878
[ Scoffs ]

18:07.878 --> 18:09.839
Look, I understand drive.

18:09.839 --> 18:11.340
I've got plenty.

18:11.340 --> 18:14.468
That's just...not where
it's pointed anymore.

18:15.845 --> 18:20.308
I get that. I ‐‐ I think
it's better to make some money.

18:20.308 --> 18:22.268
I‐I want options.

18:22.268 --> 18:24.604
[ Laughing ] You're 14.
You're all options.

18:24.604 --> 18:27.106
For JJ, later.

18:27.106 --> 18:31.110
Do I help?
Is ‐‐ Is there a plan?

18:31.110 --> 18:32.528
I want to be ready.

18:32.528 --> 18:33.904
You worry about
that stuff?

18:37.491 --> 18:40.411
Yeah, I just wanted
to talk about my windows.

18:43.748 --> 18:46.125
Still not sure why you wanted to
take the test, Kenneth, but...

18:46.125 --> 18:47.877
Mine doesn't matter.
[ Chuckles ]

18:47.877 --> 18:49.003
But you're probably curious
what I got.

18:50.171 --> 18:52.048
81%.
Well, how do you feel?

18:53.549 --> 18:56.427
"It's not a 92%,
but it's mine."

18:56.427 --> 18:58.929
Yeah, you see what you can do
all my yourself?

18:58.929 --> 19:00.181
I'm so proud of you,
darling.

19:00.181 --> 19:01.557
See, I told you.

19:01.557 --> 19:03.059
All right, I'm gonna
see you two at home.

19:03.059 --> 19:04.602
Kenneth, I know
you're dying

19:04.602 --> 19:05.853
to tell someone your score,
aren't you?

19:05.853 --> 19:07.605
Yeah, I kind of am.

19:07.605 --> 19:08.731
Yeah. Cheers.

19:08.731 --> 19:12.151
♪♪

19:12.151 --> 19:13.819
Hey, is JJ here?

19:13.819 --> 19:14.612
[ Door closes ]

19:14.612 --> 19:15.696
Hey, Maya?

19:15.696 --> 19:17.657
Yes, my darling.
We should talk.

19:17.657 --> 19:20.326
Ray asked me some questions,
and I didn't know the answers.

19:20.326 --> 19:22.870
Was it trivia?
Ugh, Ray, I've told you ‐‐

19:22.870 --> 19:24.288
don't make your dad
feel stupid.

19:24.288 --> 19:25.539
It's all right, darling.
It's over now.

19:25.539 --> 19:27.541
It's about JJ.

19:27.541 --> 19:29.001
Down the line,
what his life will look like,

19:29.001 --> 19:30.753
what he'll need after us.

19:32.171 --> 19:34.090
A‐Are we doing this?

19:34.090 --> 19:36.509
Finally, I want to
talk about this, too.

19:36.509 --> 19:38.511
Bloody hell.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.012
I thought you were just taking
him to see the windows.

19:41.389 --> 19:42.932
Well, you did it, bud.

19:42.932 --> 19:44.850
First step,
big things to follow.

19:44.850 --> 19:46.060
Sky's the limit.

19:47.353 --> 19:50.398
"I'd like to go in
myself."

19:50.398 --> 19:51.899
Oh.

19:51.899 --> 19:53.109
Mr. Independence.

19:54.860 --> 19:58.197
Doors are
flying open already.

19:58.948 --> 20:02.868
Can he drive, go to college,
maybe start a family of his own?

20:02.868 --> 20:06.372
Ray: And once you guys are gone,
whatever he wants to do,

20:06.372 --> 20:07.623
who's gonna help him?

20:07.623 --> 20:10.042
[ Exhales ]
Uh, where's JJ gonna live?

20:10.042 --> 20:11.752
What kind of help will he need?

20:11.752 --> 20:13.421
We don't know.

20:13.421 --> 20:14.922
Will you two be a part of it?
I hope so.

20:14.922 --> 20:17.383
Maya:
I mean, realistically,

20:17.383 --> 20:20.386
is your brother ever gonna be
able to live on his own?

20:21.554 --> 20:23.222
Probably not.

20:27.017 --> 20:29.478
Hey. [ Chuckles ]
How'd you get here?

20:32.231 --> 20:33.482
"We need to talk."

20:34.567 --> 20:35.568
Of course.

20:35.568 --> 20:37.153
Come in.

20:41.699 --> 20:42.700
I got a 98%.

20:46.162 --> 20:47.621
So, who was right?

20:47.621 --> 20:49.415
All of you, who couldn't just
give the kid a shot?

20:49.415 --> 20:52.793
Or the one person
who looked in his heart

20:52.793 --> 20:55.212
and said, "Let's shred"?

20:55.212 --> 20:57.381
Oh, that's good.
That's so good.

20:57.381 --> 21:01.469
Uh...he handed the boy
his test score.

21:01.469 --> 21:08.434
A lone tear slid down
young HJ's face.

21:08.434 --> 21:12.146
A phrase fought its way
to the boy's lips.

21:12.146 --> 21:16.066
He summoned his strength
and uttered his first words.

21:16.066 --> 21:17.818
Math Teacher:
Your script sucks!

21:17.818 --> 21:19.361
Damn it, Greg!
Where are you?!
